text.tspan: Probability of mismanaged plastic waste being emitted to the ocean,
Mismanaged plastic waste is waste that is not recycled, incinerated, or kept in sealed landfills. It includes materials burned
in open pits, dumped into seas or open waters, or disposed of in unsanitary landfills and dumpsites. A country's total does
not include waste that is exported overseas, which may be at higher risk of entering the ocean.
